  Sihle Malaza told Lowvelder on Tuesday that students were upset because “we don’t have enough accommodation and the university does not want to pay the accredited accommodation off campus.” “We spoke to management since February but they are ignorant about our problems. Closing the gates and striking was our last option,” Malaza said. The Fulbright American Scholarship information session had to be cancelled yesterday due to these protests. The gates of the university are still blocked by the students. Also read: Listeriosis scare just bad university food.